  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuizManagerArun
  questions:
  - questionText: The Panchatantra (sanskrit) is _________________
    option1: ...one of two great ithihasas from India.
    option2: ...the story of Rama.
    option3: ...the story of the Pandavas and the Khauravas
    option4: ...an ancient collection of animal fables.
    option1IsCorrect: 0
    option2IsCorrect: 0
    option3IsCorrect: 0
    option4IsCorrect: 1
    questionAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: e380920f27e3e8e40bad5576da7acff4, type: 3}
    questionVideo: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 0ee7967fe06234e45a95f759c6fba335, type: 3}
    optionStartTime: 5
  - questionText: 2. How many Tantras does the Panchatrantra have?
    option1: Twenty-five
    option2: Two
    option3: Five
    option4: Ten
    option1IsCorrect: 0
    option2IsCorrect: 0
    option3IsCorrect: 1
    option4IsCorrect: 0
    questionAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 07910f8008512974cb6d68320c48f3d9, type: 3}
    questionVideo: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 2b8d48f9bf9637944b2d3ea0e84b1b9f, type: 3}
    optionStartTime: 6
  - questionText: 3. Who is the author of th Panchatantra?
    option1: Rohit Sharma
    option2: Vishnu Sharma
    option3: Vyasa
    option4: J.K. Rowling
    option1IsCorrect: 0
    option2IsCorrect: 1
    option3IsCorrect: 0
    option4IsCorrect: 0
    questionAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 39eb7b11106532149a9e5c9cab49266f, type: 3}
    questionVideo: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 54c743791a4a12242815d31f9b01c627, type: 3}
    optionStartTime: 6
  - questionText: 4. What does the Panchatantra teach us ?
    option1: 'Niti Shastra  '
    option2: 'Mathematics  '
    option3: 'How to fight wars  '
    option4: Artha Shastra
    option1IsCorrect: 1
    option2IsCorrect: 0
    option3IsCorrect: 0
    option4IsCorrect: 0
    questionAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 2d828ee6ea971c648a26abad6c00848f, type: 3}
    questionVideo: {fileID: 32900000, guid: b28f4ad6748edc846b99ce1cafe8fd13, type: 3}
    optionStartTime: 6
  - questionText: 5. What is a rough translation of the word Niti ?
    option1: Being Neat
    option2: 'Truth '
    option3: common sense
    option4: nice movie
    option1IsCorrect: 0
    option2IsCorrect: 0
    option3IsCorrect: 1
    option4IsCorrect: 0
    questionAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 6d5f929186f865d40ac5c9ab3174d70d, type: 3}
    questionVideo: {fileID: 32900000, guid: cd5d4a4f938796d4dbc02103c663331a, type: 3}
    optionStartTime: 8
  - questionText: 6. Which principles does Niti Shastra incorporate? (Select all
      answers that are correct)
    option1: I need security,money and good friends
    option2: I need ice cream
    option3: I need to exercise my intelligence
    option4: I need to be capable of firm action.
    option1IsCorrect: 0
    option2IsCorrect: 0
    option3IsCorrect: 1
    option4IsCorrect: 0
    questionAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 45f71912a6ec4f34b9c97af59dc30fd7, type: 3}
    questionVideo: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 727e1bbc3ec96594594637f18ddb4a15, type: 3}
    optionStartTime: 7
  - questionText: 7. Who was the King of Mahilaropya?
    option1: Duryodhan
    option2: Shiv Shakthi
    option3: Rajinikanth
    option4: Amara Shakthi
    option1IsCorrect: 0
    option2IsCorrect: 0
    option3IsCorrect: 0
    option4IsCorrect: 1
    questionAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: ae8ff3c98755322488f2123a6cd1f802, type: 3}
    questionVideo: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 125ab8e1236193e4e97c09774b151f33, type: 3}
    optionStartTime: 6
  - questionText: 8. Why was the king sad?
    option1: His three sons did not like ice cream
    option2: His three sons were gullible
    option3: His three sons were smarter than him
    option4: His three sons were too lazy to go on vacation with him.
    option1IsCorrect: 0
    option2IsCorrect: 1
    option3IsCorrect: 0
    option4IsCorrect: 0
    questionAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 031689546fb9f1944a6620c3e4c2c707, type: 3}
    questionVideo: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 8327c55c5f50e3144879a1289fc047c5, type: 3}
    optionStartTime: 5.5
  - questionText: 9. What were the names of the King's sons? (Select all answers
